properties.growth_insight_description: Partner Engineering & Science may be growing as evidenced by their active role in thought leadership within the real estate industry, which is highlighted by multiple articles presenting the company as a thought leader. The company's involvement in addressing topics such as healthcare real estate opportunities, property resilience in the face of insurance crises, energy efficiency, and sustainability measures to increase property value, and the conversion of office and retail spaces to affordable housing indicates a strategic focus on key industry trends and challenges. Furthermore, the repeated mention of the company in various articles suggests that it is maintaining a visible and influential presence in its industry, which can be indicative of growth.

about_short_description.short_description: Partner is a national environmental and engineering consulting firm focusing on real estate due diligence, providing Phase.

product.name: Phase I Environmental Site Assessments
product.description: An assessment to identify potential or existing environmental contamination liabilities of a property.

product.name: Phase II Subsurface Investigations
product.description: Investigations involving soil, groundwater, and vapor sampling to confirm the presence of contamination.

product.name: Property Condition Assessments
product.description: Evaluations of the current condition of a property’s major systems and components.

product.name: ALTA / NSPS Land Title Surveys
product.description: Surveys to locate recorded and non-recorded matters affecting property ownership and to meet title insurer requirements.

product.name: Construction Inspections & Quality Testing
product.description: Inspections and testing to ensure construction quality and compliance with specifications.

product.name: Forensic Geotechnical Evaluations & Expert Witness
product.description: Evaluations and expert opinions on structural and geotechnical integrity for legal or insurance claims.
